          { q: 'Is hydronic heating gas or electric?', a: 'It can be either. Traditional hydronic systems use a gas boiler to heat the water. Our system uses an electric heat pump instead, which is roughly three times more efficient than gas and can be powered by your solar panels. This means your heating and cooling can run on free solar electricity during the day.' },
